WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:04.334
CHLOE:
Previously on Smallville:

00:04.505 --> 00:07.087
CLARK: What am I looking at?
JIMMY: Well, uh, it's a person.

00:07.257 --> 00:09.248
This blur saved Lois
from becoming roadkill?

00:09.718 --> 00:11.254
See, that's how good he is.

00:11.428 --> 00:13.760
This pulp rag lives or dies
by my column.

00:13.931 --> 00:15.262
Now, you get it done today...

00:15.432 --> 00:18.924
...or you're gonna be decorating bathrooms
in strip malls.

00:20.187 --> 00:23.099
You wanna rise above sea level,
you better sharpen those teeth.

00:23.273 --> 00:24.934
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

00:26.527 --> 00:30.691
You will eradicate the other Kryptonian,
and then the rest of the planet.

00:30.864 --> 00:33.355
I am not going to hurt anyone.

00:33.534 --> 00:34.694
You have no free will.

00:34.868 --> 00:37.359
And you are destined to become
what you really are.

00:39.123 --> 00:40.863
Doomsday.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.242
CHLOE:
No way. I can't believe it.

00:45.421 --> 00:48.413
I thought, just for a minute,
someone needed me.

00:48.590 --> 00:49.796
I'm sure he needs you.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.875
-How do you know?
-Because I know Clark.

00:56.807 --> 00:57.922
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:12.740 --> 01:13.729
Aw.

01:14.700 --> 01:18.192
Great, thank you! Nice to be back!

01:19.371 --> 01:20.486
Lois.

01:20.664 --> 01:23.576
Are you kidding me?
Now you show up.

01:23.751 --> 01:27.539
The one time I actually depend on you,
you ﬂake on picking me up from the airport?

01:27.713 --> 01:29.374
I am really sorry.

01:29.548 --> 01:30.788
LOIS:
Sorry?

01:30.966 --> 01:34.003
"Sorry" doesn't buy back
that last three hours I spent...

01:34.178 --> 01:37.887
...standing in a downpour...

01:39.099 --> 01:42.557
-...watching cheesy curbside reunions.
-I can explain.

01:42.728 --> 01:44.844
You e-mailed last night
to say you'd be there.

01:45.022 --> 01:47.855
What? Do I need to tie a string
around your ﬁnger myself?

01:48.025 --> 01:49.515
But I got held up at work.

01:49.693 --> 01:52.025
I ﬁnished one thing,
something else would come up.

01:52.196 --> 01:55.188
You're a reporter, Smallville.
You're not saving the world.

01:55.365 --> 01:57.617
I know. I should have called.

01:58.285 --> 01:59.900
Look, I get it.

02:00.078 --> 02:01.909
You have other things on your mind.

02:02.080 --> 02:05.823
I don't expect to be the person
at the top of your priority list.

02:18.931 --> 02:20.387
LINDA:
Clark Kent.

02:20.557 --> 02:23.765
He can save an entire city
in the blink of an eye.

02:23.936 --> 02:28.726
But when it comes to ladies, the
Red-Blue Blur still drives with the brakes on.

02:29.566 --> 02:31.227
Linda Lake.

02:31.401 --> 02:34.143
-What are you doing here?
-Watching you.

02:34.321 --> 02:36.061
Impressive as always.

02:36.240 --> 02:39.073
You're a murderer.
You should be in prison.

02:39.243 --> 02:41.609
The police cleared my name.

02:41.787 --> 02:45.575
Besides, there's no prison sentence
worse than where I've been...

02:45.749 --> 02:48.286
...circling the drain of obscurity.

02:48.585 --> 02:49.791
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

02:50.462 --> 02:52.043
I'm a nobody, Kent.

02:52.214 --> 02:55.752
Two years living underground
dried up my prophetic pen.

02:55.926 --> 03:00.169
But I'm ready to make another splash.

03:00.347 --> 03:04.135
-Haven't your stories ruined enough lives?
-Oh, no. Heh.

03:04.309 --> 03:06.220
It's different this time.

03:06.395 --> 03:10.604
I want to be the voice
of the Red-Blue Blur.

03:11.149 --> 03:12.685
Every rescue.

03:12.860 --> 03:14.771
Every takedown.

03:14.945 --> 03:19.905
Every kitten that you rescue from a tree...

03:20.075 --> 03:22.066
...you leak the story to me ﬁrst.

03:22.244 --> 03:26.533
My name will be known alongside yours
in papers around the globe.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.243
Chloe was right.

03:28.417 --> 03:29.623
You are crazy.

03:31.211 --> 03:33.543
I prefer ambitious.

03:33.714 --> 03:38.799
In fact,
I spent a few hours of my morning...

03:38.969 --> 03:41.585
...writing your life story.

03:43.307 --> 03:46.265
Partner with me, I'll shred it.

03:46.435 --> 03:48.096
You turn your back on me...

03:48.270 --> 03:52.479
...and the world reads
about little orphan alien.

03:53.442 --> 03:55.728
We've gone through this before.
I'll stop you.

03:56.278 --> 03:57.984
Not this time.

03:58.155 --> 04:00.646
You'll make a great headline, Kent.

05:10.227 --> 05:11.262
Clark?

05:11.436 --> 05:12.596
Hey.

05:12.771 --> 05:14.511
Can I raid your DVD collection?

05:14.690 --> 05:19.184
Jimmy's being transferred to Met Gen
and I don't think he's into a chick ﬂick.

05:19.528 --> 05:21.143
You okay?

05:21.321 --> 05:23.232
Linda Lake is back.

05:23.407 --> 05:24.567
What?

05:24.741 --> 05:28.074
I thought that water snake
slithered back into her swamp.

05:28.245 --> 05:30.827
If I don't give an exclusive scoop
on all of my saves...

05:30.998 --> 05:34.911
...she's gonna expose me.
My name, my face, everything.

05:35.085 --> 05:37.576
Oh, my God. Okay.

05:37.754 --> 05:40.086
Well, the H20 is obviously
gone to her head...

05:40.257 --> 05:43.590
...and we need to ﬁgure out a way
to kill that story once and for all.

05:43.760 --> 05:46.046
Well, she's got a back-up plan, Chloe.

05:46.221 --> 05:48.928
Whether we stop her or not
she's gonna release my identity.

05:51.518 --> 05:53.304
So I'm going public.

05:53.478 --> 05:55.264
On my terms.

05:55.814 --> 05:57.770
Whoa, Clark.

05:57.941 --> 06:02.184
Okay, I realize that after Lana left,
you really buried yourself in patrol duty...

06:02.362 --> 06:07.106
...and there's nothing wrong with that,
but to come out waving the ﬂag...

06:07.284 --> 06:08.694
...I mean, that's huge.

06:08.869 --> 06:12.282
Chloe, I always thought
that I would live in secret forever.

06:12.914 --> 06:16.907
But you convinced me that Jimmy's picture
of the Red-Blue Blur was a symbol of hope.

06:17.335 --> 06:21.795
Yeah, well, the world's out-of-focus
superhero didn't have an address...

06:21.965 --> 06:24.877
...or a family, or a face.

06:25.052 --> 06:26.633
Are you sure that you're ready...

06:26.803 --> 06:30.295
...to have all of your intimate details
made into the banner headline?

06:30.474 --> 06:32.214
Well, I don't have a choice.

06:32.392 --> 06:35.225
This way, I control the way my story
comes out in the press.

06:35.395 --> 06:40.731
Right, because the paparazzi are famous
for respecting people's privacy. Clark.

06:41.068 --> 06:45.232
-We can stop her, there's always a way.
-No, Chloe, this time is different.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.487
Even ifl agreed
to be Linda Lake's puppet...

06:47.657 --> 06:50.319
...eventually she will stab me in the back
and expose me.

06:50.494 --> 06:52.109
I need to stay ahead of her.

06:52.287 --> 06:55.154
Not only for me,
but for everyone else's sake.

06:56.291 --> 06:57.827
Even in a world this advanced...

06:58.001 --> 07:01.334
...people are still pretty backwards
when it comes to accepting change.

07:01.505 --> 07:04.668
I know, Chloe, but when the
Red-and-Blue Blur hit the front page...

07:04.841 --> 07:06.172
...people accepted it.

07:06.343 --> 07:08.755
And maybe they're ready to accept me.

07:11.348 --> 07:14.010
There could be an upside to all this,
you know.

07:14.392 --> 07:18.431
For the ﬁrst time in my life,
I may actually be able to be myself.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.364
Can I ask you what you're doing?

07:36.164 --> 07:39.201
Davis Bloome. I'm one of the, uh, EMTs.

07:39.668 --> 07:41.033
I've never seen you before.

07:41.211 --> 07:43.543
Oh, I've been out for a few weeks.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.705
Do you wanna explain this?

07:50.095 --> 07:53.383
-l'm just restocking my rig.
-Antipsychotics.

07:53.557 --> 07:55.468
Used for multiple personalities.

07:55.642 --> 07:58.725
Yeah, not exactly
your latest designer drug, is it?

07:59.729 --> 08:00.718
[SIGHS]

08:03.066 --> 08:05.978
I'm sorry. I hope whoever it's for,
they get the help they need.

08:06.153 --> 08:07.563
Trust me, so do I.

08:16.955 --> 08:18.911
LOIS:
Hey, Jess.

08:20.125 --> 08:21.831
Here, thanks.

08:24.421 --> 08:25.752
[SIGHS]

08:26.756 --> 08:28.587
Can I talk to you?

08:29.426 --> 08:32.088
Wow, what is that noise?
ls someone talking?

08:32.262 --> 08:34.594
Lois, you can't ignore me forever.

08:34.764 --> 08:38.052
Could be worse. You could be ignored
in a three-hour downpour.

08:40.312 --> 08:41.927
I want you to write my story.

08:42.105 --> 08:43.606
[SIGHS]

08:43.773 --> 08:48.062
No offense, but I've long since graduated
from the Ionely-seeking-lonelier classiﬁeds.

08:48.236 --> 08:51.273
-lt's a pretty interesting one.
-C|ark, I'm busy here.

08:51.448 --> 08:53.780
You may have forgotten me,
the news world didn't.

08:53.950 --> 08:56.362
After the story you're about to write,
it never will.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.776
What story?

08:58.788 --> 09:01.655
I didn't forget to pick you up
at the airport, Lois.

09:02.667 --> 09:05.784
The reason I wasn't there
is because I was protecting people.

09:06.671 --> 09:07.660
[SIGHS]

09:09.716 --> 09:11.581
I'm the Red-Blue Blur.

09:16.097 --> 09:17.633
[LAUGHS]

09:17.807 --> 09:19.263
That's the best you can do.

09:19.434 --> 09:21.345
[LOIS LAUGHING]

09:22.520 --> 09:25.512
That thing that saved you
from the speeding car, that was me.

09:25.690 --> 09:29.603
That time the barn door ﬂew off,
you thought it was weather. I did that.

09:30.028 --> 09:32.064
Yeah, right. What'd you do, sneeze?

09:32.239 --> 09:33.729
-Actually--
-Clark...

09:33.907 --> 09:38.071
...next time you liquid lunch,
take the rest of the day off.

09:38.245 --> 09:39.280
Oh.

09:41.331 --> 09:42.320
Let me help you with that.

09:42.499 --> 09:44.285
[LOIS GASPING]

09:54.302 --> 09:55.337
Oh, wow!

09:56.179 --> 09:57.214
Uh.

09:57.931 --> 09:59.341
[SHOUTS]

10:05.272 --> 10:07.934
Guess I should stop
calling you Smallville.

10:26.501 --> 10:28.833
You're speechless.
That's never a good thing.

10:30.922 --> 10:35.006
The disappearing acts,
the half-baked excuses.

10:35.635 --> 10:40.299
All this time, I just coughed it up to
a classic case of Peter Pan syndrome but....

10:43.226 --> 10:45.387
You're the opposite.

10:46.062 --> 10:47.563
You're like...

10:49.232 --> 10:50.221
[CHUCKLES]

10:50.400 --> 10:51.515
...a hero?

10:53.069 --> 10:56.561
Look, Lois. This is a lot to take in...

10:57.282 --> 11:01.400
...all at once, but I wanted you to hear from
me before you heard it from anyone else.

11:02.078 --> 11:03.864
So why am I the ﬁrst one you told?

11:06.249 --> 11:07.580
Actually, Lois, you're not.

11:11.212 --> 11:12.918
Lana and Chloe already know.

11:13.923 --> 11:15.003
Oh.

11:15.175 --> 11:17.166
Someone's had a busy morning.

11:19.304 --> 11:20.714
They've known for years.

11:24.392 --> 11:25.973
Right. Of course.

11:26.144 --> 11:27.384
[SIGHS]

11:30.482 --> 11:32.438
Start at the beginning.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.069
What guns you got in your arsenal?

11:40.617 --> 11:43.609
I guess I might as well
just throw it all out there.

11:44.662 --> 11:46.402
I can blast ﬁre out of my eyes.

11:50.668 --> 11:52.374
Okay.

11:54.464 --> 11:57.456
I can hear a dog barking
from 10 miles away.

11:57.634 --> 12:00.751
I can see through objects.
I can run faster than the speed of sound.

12:00.929 --> 12:01.964
LOIS:
Wait.

12:02.138 --> 12:03.127
Rewind.

12:03.306 --> 12:04.386
[CHUCKLES]

12:06.309 --> 12:11.645
Expand on your whole
see-through-things thing.

12:12.148 --> 12:13.934
No, Lo, l--

12:14.109 --> 12:16.475
Look, I have to focus.

12:20.490 --> 12:23.323
How did I not put these pieces together?

12:23.493 --> 12:25.779
I mean, I lived with you.

12:25.954 --> 12:30.573
We practically work on top of each other.
I mean, have I been high this entire time?

12:33.837 --> 12:36.453
The important thing
is that you know now.

12:37.757 --> 12:40.669
And there's no better reporter
to tell my story than you.

12:43.430 --> 12:45.261
Would you do me the honor?

12:47.851 --> 12:49.762
Consider it done.

12:51.020 --> 12:56.265
Tomorrow's front page will tell the tale
of the red-and-blue, meteor-infected hero.

12:58.194 --> 13:00.230
About the meteors....

13:03.074 --> 13:05.315
We should talk about where I'm from.

13:10.540 --> 13:13.452
[PEOPLE MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

13:25.013 --> 13:26.549
Your money is no good here.

13:26.723 --> 13:30.090
For 50 years, I've watched this city
get eaten alive by crime.

13:30.268 --> 13:32.179
But you picked us up, Kent.

13:32.353 --> 13:36.141
You reminded everybody
what it means to be good again.

13:37.901 --> 13:40.062
BOY:
Excuse me, Mr. Kent.

13:40.653 --> 13:42.063
Can I get your autograph?

13:43.573 --> 13:45.188
Sure.

13:45.533 --> 13:46.864
[CHUCKLES]

13:48.912 --> 13:50.448
Here you go.

13:50.747 --> 13:52.328
I like your outﬁt.

13:53.791 --> 13:55.452
Thanks.

14:05.136 --> 14:07.127
[ALL CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

14:10.016 --> 14:11.256
[CAR HONKS]

14:12.101 --> 14:15.093
MAN:
Hey, Kent! Way to go.

14:17.607 --> 14:20.724
Hey, Clark. Catch!

14:20.902 --> 14:22.563
[CROWD GASPS]

14:24.656 --> 14:29.366
-l'|l fall for you any day, Clark.
-You can't just do that. It's not--

14:29.536 --> 14:32.699
He just caught her. No way.
Did you guys see that?

14:33.414 --> 14:36.247
WOMAN 1: That was amazing.
WOMAN 2: You were great.

14:36.751 --> 14:38.287
You may have scooped me...

14:38.461 --> 14:40.122
...but I will have the last word.

14:40.296 --> 14:41.285
[SPLASH]

14:57.689 --> 14:59.805
You don't understand.
There has to be a room.

14:59.983 --> 15:02.690
My husband's being transferred here.
I conﬁrmed yesterday.

15:02.860 --> 15:05.476
Yesterday, our parking lots
weren't full of paparazzis...

15:05.655 --> 15:08.317
...and our hallways weren't full
of rubbemecking fans.

15:08.491 --> 15:11.699
-lt's not fair to our other patients.
-lt's not fair to Jimmy.

15:11.869 --> 15:16.329
I'm sorry, but we can't run a hospital
when everybody's clamoring for pictures.

15:16.833 --> 15:18.369
Of a guy in a neck brace?

15:18.543 --> 15:22.502
A guy in a neck brace
married to the alien's best friend.

15:34.851 --> 15:36.512
CHLOE:
Davis.

15:37.770 --> 15:40.728
-When did you get back?
-Chloe, hey.

15:40.898 --> 15:42.809
Uh, just a few days ago.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.693
I think we should talk
about what happened.

15:49.282 --> 15:50.317
You remember?

15:51.159 --> 15:54.322
Well, it's kind of hard to forget. I mean...

15:54.954 --> 15:56.160
...you kissed me.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.782
Right, yeah. Uh.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.747
I'm assuming that's what
all the phone calls were about.

16:03.921 --> 16:06.788
I sort of deleted the messages
without listening.

16:07.258 --> 16:08.634
Well, you didn't miss much.

16:08.801 --> 16:12.009
It was basically a long, rambling,
awkward apology.

16:13.139 --> 16:16.723
Look, I wasn't blowing you off.
It's just that, with Jimmy's recovery...

16:16.893 --> 16:20.556
...and then losing a chunk of my memory
after the wedding from hell, I was--

16:20.730 --> 16:22.971
Okay, see, this exactly
why I went out the town.

16:23.149 --> 16:24.389
I need to give you some space.

16:25.401 --> 16:26.902
No space is necessary.

16:27.070 --> 16:29.402
Davis, let's just forget
that this ever happened.

16:29.572 --> 16:31.733
Now, the problem is
I can't seem to do that.

16:33.618 --> 16:37.327
You have been nothing
but a good friend to me.

16:38.790 --> 16:41.247
I just-- I don't think
that will ever be enough.

16:43.544 --> 16:46.752
-So I take it friendship's off the table?
-Chloe.

16:46.923 --> 16:49.710
A friendship like ours...

16:52.261 --> 16:54.001
...it can be dangerous.

16:57.642 --> 16:59.724
I guess this is goodbye then.

17:06.984 --> 17:09.111
You actually know her?

17:09.278 --> 17:10.529
Yeah. So?

17:10.697 --> 17:13.029
So? She's famous.

17:13.199 --> 17:16.032
She's the Kryptonian's best friend.

17:24.210 --> 17:26.121
[WHISPERING]
Kryptonian.

17:31.592 --> 17:33.799
Ready to earn your stripes
as city editor?

17:33.970 --> 17:35.551
Linda Lake.

17:35.722 --> 17:37.929
Well, there's a name
I haven't seen in a while.

17:38.099 --> 17:40.761
Here to reclaim the stiletto
out of your assistant's back?

17:40.935 --> 17:45.850
Heh. We both know this news rag's
nothing more than poor man's wallpaper.

17:46.023 --> 17:49.936
Just here to make it readable again.
Clear your page one, run this.

17:50.319 --> 17:53.152
We stopped throwing your gossip grenades
years ago.

17:53.322 --> 17:56.530
Don't forget, while you were chasing
ambulances with the other cubs...

17:56.701 --> 17:58.157
...l was breaking real news.

17:58.327 --> 18:00.989
My blog had more hits
than the Chicago mob.

18:01.164 --> 18:03.496
My name was feared and revered
around the world.

18:03.666 --> 18:06.908
-l'm doing you a favor.
-Do yourself a favor, Lake.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.826
Get a new career.

18:09.505 --> 18:11.120
It's about the alien.

18:17.638 --> 18:21.597
Live from the Smallville farmhouse. Till this
morning Clark Kent lived in anonymity.

18:21.768 --> 18:24.851
Crowds have gathered and
are trying to peek at the superhero.

18:25.021 --> 18:28.809
There she is. Chloe Sullivan. What's it like
having an alien as a best friend?

18:28.983 --> 18:31.599
I'm, uh, just trying to get inside.

18:32.487 --> 18:36.947
Mom, what do you mean forced leave?
Can they even do that to a senator?

18:37.116 --> 18:41.450
Okay, look, this'll all blow over.
People just need time to adjust.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.202
All right, I'll talk to you later.

18:43.372 --> 18:44.361
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

18:44.540 --> 18:46.405
CHLOE:
Clark, it's Chloe.

18:48.711 --> 18:49.996
[REPORTERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

18:50.171 --> 18:52.583
It's like the Beatles have landed
in Smallville.

18:52.757 --> 18:53.792
You okay?

18:56.469 --> 18:59.961
Yeah, I'm ﬁne. How are you dealing
with the instant-star status?

19:00.139 --> 19:02.881
Unfortunately, my 15 minutes of fame
have no end in sight.

19:03.059 --> 19:06.847
I don't mean to add to the fanfare,
Lois was just given an editor's promotion...

19:07.021 --> 19:08.682
...and congratulations.

19:08.856 --> 19:12.519
You now have a penthouse ofﬁce
right next to Tess Mercer.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.310
ANCHOR 1 [ON TV]:
Clark Kent's not everyone '8 hero.

19:15.488 --> 19:16.853
WOMAN [ON TV]:
No.

19:20.284 --> 19:21.660
Last week...

19:22.370 --> 19:26.158
...a crane collapsed
at my husband's work site and killed him.

19:26.916 --> 19:28.872
Where was Clark Kent then?

19:30.878 --> 19:34.416
Who says he gets to choose
who lives and who dies?

19:39.637 --> 19:42.720
Clark, right now we need to focus
on ﬁnding Linda Lake.

19:42.890 --> 19:45.097
Now, I think I know why she went MIA.

19:45.268 --> 19:48.385
It turns out that Linda shared a cell block
with me in Black Creek.

19:48.563 --> 19:51.100
She can turn herself into water.
Why didn't she escape?

19:51.274 --> 19:53.265
Because electricity is her kryptonite.

19:53.442 --> 19:58.937
Linda Lake's specialized restraints discharge
a chemical-electrical bonding current.

19:59.115 --> 20:02.858
-Meaning it basically kept her solid.
-Great. All we have to do is ﬁnd her.

20:03.035 --> 20:05.287
ANCHOR 2 [ON TV]: -to a press conference
with Linda Lake.

20:05.454 --> 20:07.786
-It shouldn't be too hard.
LINDA [ON TV]: Clark Kent...

20:08.249 --> 20:13.118
...is not a hero. He's not a savior.

20:13.754 --> 20:16.040
He's not even a friend.

20:16.215 --> 20:18.877
He is the ﬁrst wave...

20:19.051 --> 20:23.135
...of an all-out alien invasion.

20:23.973 --> 20:27.636
My detailed investigation has revealed...

20:27.810 --> 20:33.146
...that Clark Kent is to blame
for meteor showers...

20:33.316 --> 20:35.272
...deadly power outages...

20:35.443 --> 20:39.482
...and an unspeakable trail
of human carnage.

20:39.655 --> 20:45.400
-When it rains it pours.
-But Smallville was home to a real hero.

20:45.578 --> 20:52.290
A hero that tried to stop this alien
before it ravaged our homeland again.

20:52.835 --> 20:54.917
And that hero....

20:55.296 --> 20:57.332
That hero was Lex Luthor.

20:59.133 --> 21:02.751
And Clark Kent killed him.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.169
[SCOFFS]

21:05.181 --> 21:07.012
She just turned me into a public enemy.

21:08.517 --> 21:09.506
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

21:09.685 --> 21:11.676
Clark, you need to leave. Now.

21:11.854 --> 21:14.436
I can straighten this out.
I'll talk to the authorities.

21:14.607 --> 21:16.723
Looks like they wanna talk to you too.

21:16.901 --> 21:20.018
This is only gonna get worse.
You need to leave while you still can.

21:20.196 --> 21:22.778
I'm not running, Chloe.
People need to know the truth.

21:22.949 --> 21:26.032
Why don't you go out the back, okay?
I'll catch up with you later.

21:28.788 --> 21:30.494
Be careful.

21:46.889 --> 21:50.677
REPORTER: --house here in Smallville.
Where we are all waiting to see....

21:50.851 --> 21:52.387
Linda is lying through her teeth.

21:52.561 --> 21:56.053
Her points line up, Clark. So why don't you
tell me who you're working with?

21:56.232 --> 21:59.224
Like I said, I'm not working with anyone.
I was sent here alone.

21:59.402 --> 22:02.610
To do what? Work on a farm?
It's pretty clear there's a bigger agenda.

22:02.780 --> 22:07.069
My father sent me here with a dying wish
that I use my abilities to protect mankind.

22:07.243 --> 22:09.359
It's what I've done,
it's what I'm gonna do.

22:09.537 --> 22:11.823
I'm sure if I ask friends,
they'll attest to that.

22:11.998 --> 22:12.987
Hmm?

22:13.165 --> 22:14.996
Friends like Lois Lane.

22:15.167 --> 22:18.751
You gave her the front page of a lifetime.

22:18.921 --> 22:22.709
She's keeping your secret. She could be
aiding and abetting an enemy of the state.

22:22.925 --> 22:26.338
No, Lois is innocent.
Everything she knows is in her story.

22:26.512 --> 22:27.718
And Chloe Sullivan?

22:28.305 --> 22:30.557
Impressive how long she kept your secret.

22:30.725 --> 22:32.761
How many other secrets
is she keeping, Clark?

22:33.394 --> 22:36.352
Look, I have been open
about everything you've asked me.

22:36.522 --> 22:39.264
And I appreciate it. I really do.

22:40.443 --> 22:43.310
I'm sure you won't have any problem
with us running some tests.

22:43.487 --> 22:45.102
CLARK:
No one agreed to any tests.

22:45.281 --> 22:47.613
Only to answer the questions
that you asked of me.

22:47.783 --> 22:48.772
[GLASS SHATTERS]

22:48.951 --> 22:52.284
Just calm down
and everything will be ﬁne, all right.

22:52.872 --> 22:54.112
No one's running any tests.

22:56.333 --> 22:57.584
[SHOUTING]

22:57.960 --> 22:59.370
Fire!

23:16.896 --> 23:19.478
Keep your car running.
The feds are after you.

23:19.648 --> 23:21.639
-What did they do to you?
-Doesn't matter.

23:21.817 --> 23:23.148
Leave Smallville now.

23:23.319 --> 23:26.311
MAN [ON RADIO]: We interrupt this
broadcast to bring you a special bulletin.

23:26.489 --> 23:29.401
Authorities are on a statewide manhunt
for Clark Kent.

23:29.575 --> 23:32.942
He is considered dangerous, unpredictable
and without remorse.

23:33.120 --> 23:36.487
Granville County has issued
a mandatory curfew of 9 pm.

23:36.665 --> 23:39.907
And urges all families with small children
to stay indoors at all times.

23:40.086 --> 23:41.542
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

23:42.630 --> 23:46.293
-Do they know about the meteor rocks?
-Not yet. They're after a way to stop me.

23:46.467 --> 23:49.504
-We have to leave town, separately.
-What?

23:49.678 --> 23:53.637
Am I losing you, Clark?
If this is goodbye, I'm not saying it.

23:53.808 --> 23:56.675
No, Chloe. When this all dies down,
I'll ﬁnd you, I promise.

23:56.852 --> 23:58.558
This isn't gonna die down, Clark.

23:58.729 --> 24:00.845
There has to be a way
we could undo everything.

24:01.023 --> 24:03.765
Can't you ask Jor-EI to orchestrate
another second chance?

24:03.943 --> 24:06.935
He's gone, Chloe. He disappeared
when the Fortress went dark.

24:07.113 --> 24:10.651
Unless you're hiding some latent power
to turn back time, I have no ideas.

24:12.326 --> 24:13.361
The Legion.

24:14.370 --> 24:16.986
They gave me a ring
that makes time travel possible.

24:17.164 --> 24:19.871
I hid it in the barn.
I never thought I'd have to use it.

24:20.042 --> 24:22.704
You think you can go back
to before your story broke?

24:22.878 --> 24:24.994
The Legion went back
a thousand years using it.

24:25.923 --> 24:29.541
I don't need to remind you what happened
last time you turned back the clock.

24:29.718 --> 24:31.800
There's always a consequence.

24:33.305 --> 24:37.014
The world fears me, Chloe.
As long as they know who I am...

24:37.601 --> 24:39.592
...I can't help them.

24:40.980 --> 24:43.016
I don't have a choice.

24:54.410 --> 24:57.902
Clark, call me. Whatever trash these people
are spreading about you...

24:58.080 --> 25:01.288
...you can count on me to ﬁre back,
guns blazing.

25:02.418 --> 25:06.036
You sit across from the guy, Lane.
How slow are you?

25:12.094 --> 25:14.085
Oh, hell no.

25:17.600 --> 25:19.511
Hold that elevator.

25:20.895 --> 25:21.884
[SIGHS]

25:25.107 --> 25:29.771
Last I checked, stories required
these little things called facts.

25:30.154 --> 25:34.614
The city editor is willing to print your ﬁction,
but Tess Mercer will gladly run my rebuttal.

25:34.783 --> 25:38.116
I'm sorry, Katie,
I'm gonna have to call you back.

25:38.287 --> 25:41.074
My connection just took on
a terrible whining sound.

25:41.790 --> 25:42.779
Okay, thanks.

25:42.958 --> 25:44.073
[SIGHS]

25:44.627 --> 25:45.787
Katie Couric.

25:46.462 --> 25:49.795
You see a parade
and you just have to rain on it, don't you?

25:49.965 --> 25:53.708
You can't stand the fact that there are
actually good people in this world.

25:57.473 --> 26:00.260
If your boyfriend
really cared about saving people...

26:01.644 --> 26:03.475
...he would have done things my way.

26:03.938 --> 26:05.894
People looked up to him.

26:06.065 --> 26:08.306
He could have been the hero
they always needed.

26:08.859 --> 26:10.690
Funny thing about people...

26:10.861 --> 26:13.648
...the only thing they love
more than building up heroes...

26:13.822 --> 26:15.562
...is tearing them down.

26:20.621 --> 26:22.703
Tess, what were you think--?

26:22.873 --> 26:25.489
OFFICER 1: She's up here.
OFFICER 2 [ON RADIO]: Roger that.

26:26.043 --> 26:29.661
Ms. Lane, we need to speak with you
regarding matters of national security.

26:29.838 --> 26:33.001
Without my lawyer, you're not
gonna hear me so much as hiccup.

26:34.218 --> 26:36.709
[TASER CLICKS AND POWERS UP]

26:43.102 --> 26:46.720
LOIS: You shouldn't be here.
The bloodhounds will be snifﬁng you out.

26:46.897 --> 26:50.230
It's okay. This sounds crazy,
but in a few moments, this will all be over.

26:50.401 --> 26:53.108
Okay, try me. My shock threshold
is pretty high right now.

26:53.279 --> 26:56.646
Lois, I have a ring that allows me to go
to any moment in time.

26:58.033 --> 27:02.026
I'm gonna go back to before Linda Lake
ever wrote that article.

27:02.204 --> 27:05.037
The world isn't ready to accept
someone like me.

27:06.333 --> 27:08.574
Then stay and ﬁght back.

27:08.752 --> 27:11.494
Look, give people a chance
to see who you really are.

27:11.672 --> 27:14.789
It's too late, Lois.
My whole life, I've seemed different.

27:16.260 --> 27:20.003
Some people spend their entire lives...

27:20.180 --> 27:22.592
...looking for a way to stand out.

27:23.267 --> 27:26.851
To be a person
that anybody would call special.

27:28.314 --> 27:30.054
When you ﬁrst told me who you were...

27:31.900 --> 27:34.482
...my thought was, "Anyone but Clark."

27:35.112 --> 27:38.479
And not because of the alien thing.
I've known enough guys to know...

27:38.657 --> 27:42.866
...that you can be born on Terra Firrna
and be light-years from normal.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.653
Lois, you don't have to explain. I get it.

27:46.498 --> 27:48.580
No, you don't.

27:50.044 --> 27:51.033
[SIGHS]

27:51.587 --> 27:55.079
How can someone with x-ray vision
be so blind?

27:58.552 --> 28:01.294
I've been down the hero road before.

28:02.848 --> 28:05.681
And every time, I made a giant U-turn.

28:08.520 --> 28:10.351
But this....

28:10.856 --> 28:13.393
This was different.

28:15.027 --> 28:17.439
And this time, it will be different, Lois.

28:17.613 --> 28:20.025
When I do this,
no one's gonna remember who I am.

28:21.950 --> 28:24.566
And when you hit your reset button...

28:27.331 --> 28:29.993
...you're not gonna tell me your secret,
are you?

28:33.962 --> 28:35.748
I'm
sorry

28:38.384 --> 28:40.045
It's okay.

28:41.970 --> 28:44.222
Why should I think I'm special?

28:47.184 --> 28:48.890
Clark.

28:51.730 --> 28:53.311
I understand.

28:55.859 --> 28:58.191
Lois, you don't understand.

29:00.239 --> 29:02.651
It's because you are special.

29:10.082 --> 29:11.993
I have to go.

29:24.221 --> 29:25.677
LOIS: Clark!
CLARK: Ugh.

29:26.348 --> 29:28.009
[G ROANS]

29:29.268 --> 29:31.133
Lois?

29:32.855 --> 29:35.187
Looking for this?

29:56.545 --> 29:57.534
[G ROANING]

29:57.713 --> 30:00.625
Davis. Oh, my God. What happened?

30:00.799 --> 30:04.337
Chloe, I am so sorry. It's all a lie.
I thought that I could stop it.

30:04.511 --> 30:06.467
Davis, look at me.
Tell me what's going on.

30:06.638 --> 30:08.299
-l'm gonna get help.
-No, you can't.

30:08.474 --> 30:10.385
Nothing helps.

30:10.559 --> 30:12.891
-What are these?
-Oh, jeez. I've built a tolerance.

30:13.061 --> 30:15.848
-I can't control it anymore.
-Control what?

30:17.232 --> 30:18.483
The beast.

30:21.111 --> 30:23.898
You must have blacked it out.
You were in the Arctic with me.

30:27.910 --> 30:30.026
What are you saying?
The other Kryptonian?

30:30.204 --> 30:33.037
There's only one Kryptonian.
There's only Clark.

30:34.374 --> 30:36.751
I am Kryptonian.

30:38.003 --> 30:39.163
[DAVIS GASPING]

30:41.924 --> 30:43.255
You're Doomsday.

30:44.259 --> 30:47.376
I was sent to this planet to kill Clark.

30:49.306 --> 30:51.012
You stay away from him.

30:51.183 --> 30:53.720
You have to warn him.
Something's been drawing me back.

30:53.894 --> 30:57.887
I thought that it was you,
but, no, it was Clark.

30:59.441 --> 31:01.022
[G ROWLS]

31:02.778 --> 31:04.109
Davis, your eyes.

31:04.988 --> 31:08.947
[IN RASPY VOICE]
Chloe, run. Get out of here!

31:11.411 --> 31:13.072
[DAVIS ROARS]

31:13.247 --> 31:16.284
Lois, give a message to Clark.
He's not picking up his phone.

31:16.458 --> 31:19.074
That creature that was at my wedding
is Davis Bloome.

31:19.253 --> 31:20.959
And he's coming for Clark.

31:25.842 --> 31:27.833
[SHOUTING]

31:44.528 --> 31:47.144
I used to think a lot about rings.

31:47.322 --> 31:50.940
I thought getting one meant
I'd found true happiness.

31:51.118 --> 31:54.781
But there is no such thing
as true happiness in this world, is there?

31:54.955 --> 31:57.662
Not when you only see the bad in people.

31:57.958 --> 31:59.448
[CLARK GASPING]

32:00.252 --> 32:02.584
Look how fast they turned on you.

32:02.754 --> 32:05.006
One second, you're on top of the world.

32:05.173 --> 32:06.253
And the next...

32:06.425 --> 32:10.088
...it's as if your life story's written
in someone else's blood.

32:10.262 --> 32:13.675
Not that I care.
This trumps your blur any day.

32:13.849 --> 32:15.430
That ring, it's dangerous.

32:15.601 --> 32:19.514
No. This ring is every journalist's dream.

32:19.688 --> 32:22.395
I'll know stories before they break.

32:22.566 --> 32:26.104
The entire world will know me.

32:28.071 --> 32:30.062
[BOTH GRUNTING]

32:45.964 --> 32:46.999
LOIS:
Clark!

32:48.383 --> 32:50.339
Lois, the rock.

32:52.137 --> 32:53.718
-Are you okay?
-l'|l be all right.

32:53.889 --> 32:55.675
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

33:01.396 --> 33:02.806
LOIS:
Clark!

33:02.981 --> 33:06.098
Chloe just called.
You're not gonna believe this.

33:06.276 --> 33:07.391
But Davis--

33:23.627 --> 33:24.867
[WHOOSH]

33:25.253 --> 33:27.209
I know what you're planning.

33:28.298 --> 33:30.163
Mr. Kent.

33:30.342 --> 33:32.253
I was just thinking about you.

33:32.427 --> 33:34.713
Two years is too long to go
without a visit.

33:35.263 --> 33:36.924
You're not gonna run my story.

33:38.642 --> 33:41.429
Oh, your story?

33:41.603 --> 33:44.436
Oh, so now you're notjust super,
you're psychic.

33:44.606 --> 33:46.471
I'm a journalist now.

33:46.650 --> 33:48.436
I brought you my latest work.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.566
It's about all the murders
you've committed.

33:55.617 --> 33:57.824
People are gonna know
who you really are.

33:57.994 --> 33:59.530
And your word will mean nothing.

34:01.832 --> 34:03.197
You're going to jail.

34:04.793 --> 34:06.704
I don't think so.

34:11.174 --> 34:13.165
[G ROANING]

34:29.651 --> 34:31.858
No one can ever know my name.

34:37.409 --> 34:39.024
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

34:46.168 --> 34:47.578
Some things never change.

34:47.753 --> 34:51.496
I've been gone a month,
and you still drive in the granny lane.

34:53.467 --> 34:55.173
CLARK:
You're welcome for the ride, Lois.

34:55.343 --> 34:58.176
Did I mention that I missed
your ongoing commentary?

34:58.346 --> 35:01.179
No, actually, aside from asking me
what the speed limit was...

35:01.349 --> 35:04.307
...you barely said a word
on the way home.

35:04.478 --> 35:08.642
Or since I've been gone, unless you count
your three 10-second voicemails.

35:08.815 --> 35:11.978
Lois, you know, after the wedding,
things got a little crazy.

35:12.152 --> 35:16.942
Heh, things got a little crazy
before all hell broke loose, let's face it.

35:19.367 --> 35:21.449
Or we could not face it...

35:21.620 --> 35:24.453
...and just forget
that it ever almost happened.

35:26.541 --> 35:29.658
I think it's a pretty
complicated conversation, Lois.

35:32.088 --> 35:35.000
We don't have to
overanalyze anything now.

35:36.968 --> 35:39.675
I'm gonna work off my jet lag
later on tonight at the café.

35:39.846 --> 35:43.134
You wanna come by for a coffee, cool.
If not, let's just say I get it.

35:44.309 --> 35:45.810
Okay.

35:46.436 --> 35:48.552
Okay. See you then.

35:49.731 --> 35:53.223
Or not. Or whatever. I'm going to work.

36:01.451 --> 36:03.863
I admit, I would've loved
to have seen Clark Kent...

36:04.037 --> 36:06.494
...as an international celebrity icon.

36:06.665 --> 36:07.950
It wasn't a pretty sight.

36:08.124 --> 36:11.366
But being a part of your entourage,
I must have had some perks, right?

36:11.545 --> 36:14.958
If you consider a complete
invasion of privacy a perk.

36:15.465 --> 36:19.253
But there was this one moment
right after I told Lois the truth about me.

36:19.427 --> 36:21.759
I thought everything would be okay.

36:22.347 --> 36:24.429
That I could have it all,
but I was wrong.

36:26.935 --> 36:30.268
You know, Clark, maybe you can
have your cape and wear it too.

36:31.022 --> 36:35.641
Say Clark Kent, the unassuming journalist,
buttoned up in a starched shirt and tie...

36:35.819 --> 36:37.935
...but then, when he's playing hero he's--

36:38.113 --> 36:42.106
Steps out of the shadow into his red
and blue, creating two separate identities?

36:42.284 --> 36:45.902
Yeah. And for the cherry on top...

36:46.079 --> 36:48.912
...you get to tell Lois the truth
and know her reaction.

36:49.082 --> 36:52.040
All of this made one thing
very clear, Chloe.

36:52.460 --> 36:54.587
Lois can never know who I really am.

36:55.547 --> 36:59.005
Is it safe to say that maybe another beneﬁt
from protecting your secret...

36:59.175 --> 37:01.587
...is getting to protect yourself
from getting hurt?

37:04.222 --> 37:06.133
I destroyed the Legion ring.

37:09.269 --> 37:11.100
Speaking of that.

37:11.271 --> 37:17.483
Controlling time is too dangerous, Chloe.
It always comes at a price.

37:19.070 --> 37:23.484
Trust me,
I'm thrilled that you got a page-one rewrite.

37:23.700 --> 37:28.785
But it kind of makes me wonder
what might have changed this time.

37:42.177 --> 37:43.462
Can I ask what you're doing?

37:45.096 --> 37:48.680
I'm Davis Bloome.
I'm one of the, uh, EMTs.

37:50.977 --> 37:53.810
Oh, well, there's actually a patient
who's looking for you.

38:06.326 --> 38:08.817
Uh, there must be some mistake.
I don't know you.

38:08.995 --> 38:12.487
While I've been puddling around Metropolis
for the last week...

38:12.666 --> 38:15.408
...l've seen lots of interesting stories.

38:15.585 --> 38:19.828
What a nice surprise
to stumble upon your dirty little secret.

38:20.966 --> 38:22.456
The painful breathing.

38:22.634 --> 38:24.295
Pale complexion.

38:25.220 --> 38:28.303
Unsightly bone protrusions.

38:37.691 --> 38:39.556
You don't know
what you're talking about.

38:39.734 --> 38:43.352
Right, you just have
a terrible skin condition.

38:43.863 --> 38:44.852
[SIGHS]

38:45.365 --> 38:46.901
What do you want from me?

38:47.075 --> 38:51.239
I want you to release the beast...

38:51.997 --> 38:54.579
...and break me out of these restraints.

38:56.501 --> 38:59.709
It doesn't exactly work like that.

39:01.339 --> 39:03.125
Don't waste your time with the pills.

39:03.299 --> 39:06.757
-l have seen what you can do.
-You don't understand.

39:06.928 --> 39:10.921
-You don't know what you're dealing with.
-No. You don't understand.

39:11.099 --> 39:13.511
I can't spend another second
trapped in a cell.

39:13.685 --> 39:16.768
Do you want me to tell Chloe
who you really are?

39:17.397 --> 39:19.513
[G ROANS]

39:21.109 --> 39:23.100
[G ROWLS]

39:23.278 --> 39:24.358
Good boy.

39:24.529 --> 39:26.440
Become the thing you're meant to be.

39:26.614 --> 39:29.105
-Stop.
-Let it go.

39:29.284 --> 39:31.775
-Shut up!
-Set me free!

39:35.123 --> 39:37.114
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

40:02.484 --> 40:04.395
Oh, my God.

41:01.209 --> 41:02.790
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

41:27.026 --> 41:28.402
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

42:29.297 --> 42:31.288
[ENGLISH SDH]
